ic Records|Republic]]\n| {{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n|-\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italy\n| December 13, 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| [[Universal Music|Universal]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://radiodate.it/radio-date/karol-g-nicki-minaj-tusa-190111-13-12-2019-radiodate/|title=Karol G - Tusa (Radio Date: 12/13/19)|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| February 11, 2020\n| [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|website=All Access Music Group|access-date=February 5, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205234129/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archivedate=February 5, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Karol G}}\n{{Nicki Minaj songs}}\n\n[[Category:2019 singles]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:Karol G songs]]\n[[Category:Nicki Minaj songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Spain]]\n[[Category:Argentina Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot Latin Songs number-one singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 song by Karol G and Nicki Minaj}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Tusa\n| cover      = Tusa.webp\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Karol G]] and [[Nicki Minaj]]\n| album      =\n| released   = {{start date|2019|11|07}}\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   = 2019\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Reggaeton]]<ref name=\"RS20191107\" />\n| length     = 3:20\n| label      =\n* [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n* [[Universal Music Latino]] \n* [[Universal Music Group]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|Keityn|[[Karol G]]|[[Nicki Minaj]]}}\n| producer   = Ovy on the Drums\n| chronology = [[Karol G]]\n| prev_title = [[China (Anuel AA song)|China]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = Follow\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n| artist     = [[Nicki Minaj]]\n| type       = singles\n| prev_title = [[Welcome to the Party (Pop Smoke song)|Welcome to the Party]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| title      = Tusa\n| year       = 2019\n| next_title = [[Nice to Meet Ya (Meghan Trainor song)|Nice to Meet Ya]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|tbneQDc2H3I|\"Tusa\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Tusa'''\" ([[Colombian Spanish#Common expressions|Colombian slang]] for \"heartache\")<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8543271/karol-g-nicki-minaj-tusa-lyric-translated-english|title=Karol G & Nicki Minaj's 'Tusa' Is for the Girl Who Can't Get Over Her Ex: English Lyric Translation||work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Roiz|first=Jessica|date=November 11, 2019|accessdate=December 30, 2019}}</ref> is a song by Colombian reggaeton singer [[Karol G]] and Trinidadian-American rapper [[Nicki Minaj]]. The song was written by Karol G, Keityn, Ovy on the Drums and Nicki Minaj, and produced by Ovy on the Drums. It was released as a single by [[Republic Records]], [[Universal Music Latino]] and [[Universal Music Group]] on November 7, 2019.\n\nIt peaked at number 42 on the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100. The song became Minaj's 106th entry on the chart and Karol G's 4th, and also extended Minaj's record for most entries on the chart by a female artist.<ref name=\"Billboard20191120\">{{cite web |last=Bustios |first=Pamela |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8544328/karol-g-nicki-minaj-debut-number-one-latin-songs |title=Karol G & Nicki Minaj's 'Tusa' Becomes First Song by Two Lead Female Artists to Debut at No. 1 on Hot Latin Songs |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=November 20, 2019 |accessdate=November 22, 2019}}</ref> The song debuted at number 56 on the [[Rolling Stone Top 100|''Rolling Stone'' Top 100]].<ref name=\"RS 100\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/songs/2019-11-08/ |title=Top 100 Songs \u2013 Nov 8, 2019 - Nov 14, 2019 |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=November 22, 2019 |accessdate=November 24, 2019}}</ref> It also reached number one in sixteen countries.\n\n==Background==\n\"Tusa\" is the first collaboration between Karol G and Minaj. On November 6, 2019, Karol G shared the artwork for the single on her social media, as well as snippets of the official music video. In an interview with ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', she told them how the collaboration came about:\n\n{{quote|She called me and said: \"I'm going to make the best rap of my life for your song\", I felt so happy. I sent her the music at 1 p.m. At 1:07 p.m., she downloaded the file, and at 8 p.m., I had the song back.<ref name=\"Billboard20191107\">{{cite web |last=Cobo |first=Leila |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8543079/karol-g-nicki-minaj-tusa-video-interview |title=Karol G Talks Enlisting a Spanish-Speaking Nicki Minaj for 'Tusa': Watch the Music Video |work=Billboard |date=November 7, 2019 |accessdate=November 24, 2019}}</ref>}}\n\n==Composition==\n\"Tusa\" is three minutes and twenty seconds long.<ref>https://music.apple.com/us/album/tusa-single/1485476559</ref> It was written by Karol G, Keityn, Ovy on the Drums and Nicki Minaj, with production by Ovy on the Drums.<ref name=\"Billboard20191120\" /> \"Tusa\" is Colombian slang for the mixture of heartache and desire for revenge felt by a person when their partner breaks up with them.<ref name=\"Billboard20191107\" /> Lyrically, Karol G's verses tell the story of a woman who struggles to forget her former boyfriend, while Minaj's rap tells the man that the woman has moved on with her life.<ref>{{cite web |last=Roiz |first=Jessica |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8543271/karol-g-nicki-minaj-tusa-lyric-translated-english |title=Karol G & Nicki Minaj's 'Tusa' Is for the Girl Who Can't Get Over Her Ex: English Lyric Translation |work=Billboard |date=November 11, 2019 |accessdate=November 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nIn the United States, \"Tusa\" debuted at number one on the [[Hot Latin Songs]], becoming the first song by two lead female artists to debut atop the chart, and also the first song by a female act in a lead role to chart at number one since 2016, when [[Shakira]]'s \"[[Chantaje]]\" featuring Maluma reached the top. It became Minaj's sixth entry on the Hot Latin Songs chart, and her second top 10, following the 2017's \"[[Krippy Kush]] (remix)\" with Farruko, Bad Bunny, 21 Savage and Rvssian.<ref>https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8544328/karol-g-nicki-minaj-debut-number-one-latin-songs</ref> It became Karol G's second number one on the Hot Latin Songs chart and Minaj's first No.1 entry on any ''Billboard'' Latin chart.<ref>https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100</ref> \n\nOn the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], the song debuted at number 78, becoming Karol's fourth chart entry and Minaj's 106th entry.<ref>https://urbanislandz.com/2019/11/19/nicki-minaj-karol-gs-tusa-creates-billboard-history/</ref> It peaked at number 42 on the Hot 100. \"Tusa\" also reached number 41 on the ''Rolling Stone'' US Top 100 Songs chart on the week ending January 30, 2020, with 67,200 sales plus track-equivalent streams.<ref>https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/songs/2019-11-08/</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for \"Tusa\" was released through Karol G's [[YouTube]] channel on November 7, 2019. It was filmed in Los Angeles and directed by American music video director Mike Ho.<ref name=\"RS20191107\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/karol-g-nicki-minaj-surprise-video-tusa-909589/|title=Karol G, Nicki Minaj Exude Glamour in Surprise New Video for 'Tusa'.|last=Exposito|first=Suzy|date=November 7, 2019|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=November 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.elespectador.com/entretenimiento/musica/tusa-la-nueva-cancion-de-karol-g-y-nicki-minaj-articulo-890228 |title=\"Tusa\", la nueva canci\u00f3n de Karol G y Nicki Minaj |newspaper=[[El Espectador]] |language=Spanish |date=November 8, 2019 |accessdate=November 24, 2019}}</ref> It has since accumulated over 700 million views with 6 million likes.\n\n==Live performances==\nOn December 8, 2019, [[Karol G]] performed \"Tusa\" at Pixel 4's Motion Sense Concert Series. <ref>https://9to5google.com/2019/11/17/pixel-4-karol-g-motion-sense-video/</ref> Karol G premiered the song on American television as she performed it at ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'' on January 10, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8547826/karol-g-tusa-performance-tonight-show-watch|title=Karol G Made Her Late-Night Debut With Violet 'Tusa' Performance on 'The Tonight Show': Watch|first=Jessica|last=Roiz|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 11, 2020|accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardargentinahot100|1|artist=Karol G|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 10, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders Tip|7|artist=Karol G / Nicki Minaj|song=Tusa|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|6|artist=Karol G / Nicki Minaj|song=Tusa|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Bolivia ([[Monitor Latino]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Print/Bolivia/general/20200309|title=Bolivia General|language=Spanish|accessdate=March 21, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321175652/http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Print/Bolivia/general/20200309|archivedate=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|98|artist=Karol G|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 4, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| 