irus (COVID-19) on the NHS website]\n* [https://www.gov.uk/coronavirus Coronavirus (COVID-19): UK government information ]\n* [https://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2020/129/contents/made The Health Protection (Coronavirus) Regulations 2020]. Legislation.gov.uk\n* [https://www.publichealth.hscni.net/publications/advice-covid-19-coronavirus Public Health Agency] \u2013 Advice on COVID-19 (coronavirus)\n* [https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/country/uk/ Worldometer UK Statistics] \u2013 Worldometer graphs and statistics for the UK\n* [https://coronavirus-global.com/uk Coronavirus United Kingdom updates and news]. United Kingdom in Coronavirus Global international portal. Available in English, French, Spanish and more.\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|short=yes}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|United Kingdom|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:January 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "Paul W", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePrisons:add wlMinistry of Justice (United Kingdom)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_United_Kingdom"}
{"title_page": "Brockport Golden Eagles football", "text_new": "{{Infobox NCAA football school\n| CurrentSeason   = \n| TeamName         = Brockport Golden Eagles\n| Image            =\n| ImageSize        = 160\n| HeadCoach = Jason Mangone\n| HeadCoachYear    = 7th\n| HCWins           = 57\n| HCLosses         = 22\n| OtherStaff       = \n| Stadium          = [[Eunice Kennedy Shriver Stadium]]\n| StadCapacity     = 10,000\n| StadSurface      = Artifcial\n| Location         = [[Brockport, New York]] \n| NCAAdivision     = III\n| Conference = [[Empire 8]]\n| ConfDivision     =\n| FirstYear        = \n| AthleticDirector = Erick Hart\n| WebsiteName      = GoBrockport.com\n| WebsiteURL       = http://www.gobrockport.com/\n| ATWins           = \n| ATLosses         = \n| ATTies           = \n| BowlWins         = 2\n| BowlLosses       = 5\n| BowlTies         = \n| NatlTitles       =\n| ConfTitles       = 4\n| DivTitles        = 1\n| Heismans         =\n| AllAmericans     = 53\n| uniform          =\n| Color1           = Green\n| Color1Hex        = 00573C\n| Color2           = Gold\n| Color2Hex        = FFC425\n| FightSong        = \n| MascotDisplay    = \n| MascotLink       = \n| MarchingBand     = \n| PagFreeLabel     = Rivals\n| PagFreeValue     = \n}}\n\n: ''For information on all State University of New York at Brockport sports, see [[Brockport Golden Eagles]]''\n\nThe '''Brockport Golden Eagles football''' program is the intercollegiate [[American football]] team for the [[State University of New York at Brockport]] located in the U.S. state of [[New York (state)|New York]]. The team competes in the [[Division III (NCAA)|NCAA Division III]] and are members of the [[Empire 8]]. The team plays its home games at the 10,000 seat [[Special Olympics Stadium|Eunice Kennedy Shriver Stadium]] in [[Brockport, New York]]. The Golden Eagles are coached by Jason Mangone.<ref name=\"team\">{{cite web| title=Brockport State Golden Eagles|publisher=d3football.com| url=http://www.d3football.com/teams/Brockport_State/index|accessdate=2013-02-01}}</ref> Brockport participates yearly in the [[Courage Bowl]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:1A1A1517.jpg|alt=Jason Mangone|thumb|Head Coach- Jason Mangone]]\nBrockport Golden Eagles football began in 1947 after the end of WWII, when veterans returning from the war began to attend the college on the GI Bill. Many of these young people had gone off to the war right after high school or during high school and wanted to have a true college experience complete with athletic teams. The first football team included center Louis F. Avino, who also came up with the team's Golden Eagles mascot. The team was led by Robert Boozer who went on to a long career as an educator and coach at Brockport, the athletic field at Special Olympic Stadium was named Bob Boozer Field in his honor in 2006. The original locker room was a cold room located under the stairwell in Heartwell Hall. Brockport made it to the NCAA DIII postseason for the first time in school history in 2000 and went four consecutive times under coach Salomone's lead.\nIn [[2002 NCAA Division III football season#Postseason|2002]], Brockport made it all the way to the NCAA quarterfinals before losing to John Carroll in overtime. After a 15 year drought, the Golden Eagles qualified for the [[2017 NCAA Division III football season#Postseason|2017 NCAA Playoffs]] following an undefeated regular season. In 2018 the Golden Eagles would once again go undefeated in the regular season and qualify for the [[2018 NCAA Division III football season#Postseason|2018 NCAA Division III Playoffs]]. The 2019 Season the Golden Eagles would once again find their way to the [[2019 NCAA Division III football season]]  playoffs with a win against Western New England and advance to play Muhlenberg.\n\n'''History in the NCAA Division III Playoffs'''\n\n{| cellpadding=\"1\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n!bgcolor=\"#00573C\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Year</span>\n!bgcolor=\"#00573C\"| <span 